---
import ToolLayout from '../../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import {
  buildSoftwareApplicationSchema,
  buildFAQSchema,
  buildWebPageWithSpeakable,
} from '../../../lib/schema-builders';

const pageTitle = 'Free Schema Markup Generator — Real PAA FAQ + JSON-LD | theStacc';
const pageDescription = 'Generate LocalBusiness, FAQ, Service, and Breadcrumb schema markup in JSON-LD. Fetch real People Also Ask questions from Google, auto-write answers with AI. 23 industry presets. Free, no signup.';
const pageUrl = 'https://thestacc.com/tools/schema-markup-generator/';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-11';

const softwareSchema = buildSoftwareApplicationSchema({
  name: 'Free Schema Markup Generator',
  description: 'Generate LocalBusiness, FAQPage, Service, and BreadcrumbList schema markup in JSON-LD. Fetch real People Also Ask questions from Google with AI-written answers. 23 industry presets for local businesses.',
  url: pageUrl,
});

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is schema markup and why does it matter for SEO?', a: 'Schema markup is structured data code (usually JSON-LD) that you add to your website to help search engines understand your content. For local businesses, it tells Google your business name, address, phone number, services, hours, and reviews in a machine-readable format. According to Google, pages with proper structured data are eligible for rich results like star ratings, FAQ dropdowns, and business panels in search results. A 2025 Search Engine Journal study found that rich results can increase click-through rates by up to 30%.' },
  { q: 'How do I add schema markup to my website?', a: 'Copy the JSON-LD code from this generator and paste it in your HTML before the closing </head> tag. In WordPress, use the "Insert Headers and Footers" plugin. In Webflow, go to Page Settings > Custom Code > Head Code. In Squarespace, go to Settings > Advanced > Code Injection > Header. In Wix, go to Settings > Custom Code. After adding the code, validate it using Google\'s Rich Results Test to confirm it works.' },
  { q: 'What schema types should a local business use?', a: 'Every local business should have four core schema types: (1) LocalBusiness schema with your specific subtype (Dentist, Plumber, Attorney, etc.), (2) FAQPage schema for common customer questions, (3) Service schema for each service you offer, and (4) BreadcrumbList schema for navigation. Combining these in a single @graph gives Google the most complete picture of your business. Most businesses only have LocalBusiness — adding all four gives you a competitive advantage.' },
  { q: 'What is the People Also Ask feature and how does this tool use it?', a: 'People Also Ask (PAA) is a Google SERP feature that shows expandable question-and-answer boxes based on real user searches. This tool fetches live PAA questions for your industry and uses AI to write professional answers. Using real PAA questions in your FAQ schema means you are answering questions that actual customers are actively searching for — dramatically increasing your chances of appearing in both PAA boxes and rich results.' },
  { q: 'Do I need schema markup for local SEO?', a: 'Yes. Schema markup is one of the strongest local SEO signals. Businesses with proper LocalBusiness schema are more likely to appear in the local pack, knowledge panels, and rich results. Google explicitly recommends JSON-LD format. According to a 2024 Whitespark study, structured data is among the top 10 ranking factors for local pack results. Without schema, Google has to guess your business details from page text.' },
  { q: 'What are rich results and how does schema trigger them?', a: 'Rich results are enhanced search listings that include extra visual elements like star ratings, FAQ dropdowns, breadcrumbs, images, and business information panels. Schema markup is the trigger — Google uses your structured data to generate these enhanced listings. FAQPage schema creates expandable Q&A boxes below your listing. AggregateRating in LocalBusiness schema shows star ratings. BreadcrumbList replaces plain URLs with clean navigation paths.' },
  { q: 'Is this schema markup generator free?', a: 'Yes, 100% free. No signup required for basic schema generation. Select your industry to auto-fill fields, customize your business details, and copy valid JSON-LD code instantly. The real People Also Ask fetch feature is also free — it uses live Google search data and AI to pre-fill your FAQ section with questions real customers are asking. Everything runs server-side; your business data is not stored.' },
  { q: 'How is this different from other schema generators?', a: 'Most schema generators give you empty templates or static preset questions. This tool fetches live People Also Ask questions from Google for your specific industry, then uses AI to write complete, professional answers. It also generates Service schema (most tools skip this), supports 23 industry-specific LocalBusiness subtypes, and includes a completeness score that shows you exactly what information you are missing. No other free tool combines real PAA data with AI answer generation.' },
  { q: 'Can I use this schema for multiple pages?', a: 'Yes, but each page should have page-specific schema. Your homepage should have your full LocalBusiness schema. Service pages should have Service schema for that specific service. FAQ pages should have FAQPage schema with relevant questions. Contact pages should include your address and geo coordinates. This tool lets you generate each type individually or combine them in a single @graph.' },
  { q: 'How long does it take for schema to appear in search results?', a: 'Google typically processes and displays schema within 3-14 days after you add it to your site. Use Google\'s Rich Results Test to validate your markup immediately. Then submit your page URL to Google Search Console for indexing. Not all schema triggers rich results — Google decides which enhancements to show based on relevance, quality, and user intent. The best way to improve your chances is to ensure your schema is complete, accurate, and matches your page content exactly.' },
];

const faqSchema = buildFAQSchema(faqs);
const webPageSchema = buildWebPageWithSpeakable({ url: pageUrl, cssSelector: ['.speakable'] });

const industries = [
  { value: '', label: 'Select your industry (auto-fills fields)' },
  { value: 'dentist', label: 'Dentist' },
  { value: 'chiropractor', label: 'Chiropractor' },
  { value: 'orthodontist', label: 'Orthodontist' },
  { value: 'optometrist', label: 'Optometrist' },
  { value: 'dermatologist', label: 'Dermatologist' },
  { value: 'plumber', label: 'Plumber' },
  { value: 'hvac', label: 'HVAC' },
  { value: 'electrician', label: 'Electrician' },
  { value: 'roofing', label: 'Roofing' },
  { value: 'landscaping', label: 'Landscaping' },
  { value: 'pest_control', label: 'Pest Control' },
  { value: 'auto_repair', label: 'Auto Repair' },
  { value: 'lawyer', label: 'Lawyer' },
  { value: 'accountant', label: 'Accountant' },
  { value: 'realtor', label: 'Real Estate Agent' },
  { value: 'insurance', label: 'Insurance Agency' },
  { value: 'financial_advisor', label: 'Financial Advisor' },
  { value: 'restaurant', label: 'Restaurant' },
  { value: 'salon', label: 'Salon / Spa' },
  { value: 'gym', label: 'Gym / Fitness' },
  { value: 'veterinarian', label: 'Veterinarian' },
  { value: 'cleaning', label: 'Cleaning Service' },
  { value: 'moving', label: 'Moving Company' },
  { value: 'other', label: 'Other / General' },
];
---

<ToolLayout
  seo={{ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, canonical: pageUrl, ogImage: '/og/tools-schema-markup-generator.webp' }}
  toolName="Free Schema Markup Generator"
  toolDescription="Generate LocalBusiness, FAQ, Service, and Breadcrumb schema in JSON-LD. Fetch real People Also Ask questions from Google, auto-write answers with AI. 23 industry presets."
  wide={true}
  softwareSchema={softwareSchema}
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
  webpageSchema={webPageSchema}
>
  <Fragment slot="tool">
    <style>
      .schema-wrap { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 28px; }
      @media (min-width: 1024px) { .schema-wrap { flex-direction: row; } }
      .schema-form-col { flex: 1.5; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; }
      .schema-preview-col { flex: 1; }
      .schema-preview-col .sticky { position: sticky; top: 24px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }

      .schema-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
      .schema-card h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 14px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
      .schema-type-option { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start; padding: 14px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 10px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s; }
      .schema-type-option:hover { border-color: var(--brand); }
      .schema-type-option.active { border-color: var(--brand); background: var(--brand-softer); }
      .schema-type-option input { margin-top: 3px; accent-color: var(--brand); }
      .schema-type-option .title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); }
      .schema-type-option .desc { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 2px; }
      .schema-type-option .badge { display: inline-block; margin-left: 6px; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
      .badge-green { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
      .badge-amber { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }

      .field { margin-bottom: 14px; }
      .field:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
      .field label { display: block; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .field input, .field select, .field textarea { width: 100%; padding: 11px 13px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-1); background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-family: inherit; }
      .field input:focus, .field select:focus, .field textarea:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--brand); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--brand-glow); }
      .field textarea { resize: vertical; min-height: 64px; }
      .field-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 14px; }
      @media (min-width: 640px) { .field-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
      .field-grid-3 { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 14px; }
      @media (min-width: 640px) { .field-grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; } }
      .req { background: #fee2e2; color: #b91c1c; padding: 2px 6px; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; }
      .rec { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; padding: 2px 6px; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; }
      .opt { background: var(--bg-soft); color: var(--text-3); padding: 2px 6px; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; }

      .section-title { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-3); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin: 18px 0 10px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; }
      .hidden { display: none !important; }

      .btn-add { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 8px 12px; background: var(--brand-softer); color: var(--brand); border: none; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
      .btn-add:hover { background: var(--brand); color: white; }
      .btn-remove { padding: 6px 10px; background: #fee2e2; color: #b91c1c; border: none; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
      .btn-remove:hover { background: #fecaca; }
      .btn-primary { width: 100%; padding: 13px 18px; background: var(--text-1); color: white; border: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; }
      .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--brand); }
      .btn-secondary { flex: 1; padding: 11px 14px; background: white; color: var(--text-1); border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; }
      .btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--brand); color: var(--brand); }

      .preview-block { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; }
      .completeness { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
      .completeness-bar-wrap { flex: 1; height: 8px; background: var(--bg-soft); overflow: hidden; }
      .completeness-bar { height: 100%; background: #22c55e; transition: width 0.3s; }
      .completeness-label { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; }
      .code-block { background: #1c1917; padding: 16px; overflow-x: auto; max-height: 420px; overflow-y: auto; }
      .code-block pre { color: #e7e5e4; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word; margin: 0; }
      .preview-actions { display: flex; gap: 10px; margin-top: 14px; }

      .paa-box { background: var(--brand-softer); border: 1px solid var(--brand-glow); padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .paa-box p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .paa-row { display: flex; gap: 8px; }
      .paa-row input { flex: 1; }
      .paa-btn { padding: 10px 14px; background: var(--brand); color: white; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
      .paa-btn:hover { background: var(--text-1); }
      .paa-status { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--brand); }

      .faq-item, .service-item, .bc-item { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 14px; margin-bottom: 10px; background: white; }
      .faq-item-head, .service-item-head, .bc-item-head { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .faq-item-head span, .service-item-head span, .bc-item-head span { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); }

      .email-modal { position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 50; display: none; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.5); backdrop-filter: blur(4px); }
      .email-modal.show { display: flex; }
      .email-modal-box { background: white; padding: 28px; max-width: 420px; width: 90%; }
      .email-modal-box h4 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .email-modal-box p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 16px; }

      .how-to ol { margin: 12px 0 0 18px; padding: 0; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.7; }
      .how-to li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .how-to code { background: var(--bg-soft); padding: 2px 5px; font-size: 12px; }
    </style>

    <div class="schema-wrap">
      <div class="schema-form-col">
        <div class="schema-card">
          <h3>Schema Types</h3>
          <label class="schema-type-option active" id="opt-local">
            <input type="checkbox" id="type-local" checked />
            <div>
              <div class="title">LocalBusiness <span class="badge badge-green">Recommended</span></div>
              <div class="desc">Name, address, phone, hours, reviews, geo coordinates</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <label class="schema-type-option" id="opt-faq">
            <input type="checkbox" id="type-faq" />
            <div>
              <div class="title">FAQPage <span class="badge badge-green">+ Real PAA</span></div>
              <div class="desc">Question and answer pairs. Fetch real Google People Also Ask questions with AI-written answers</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <label class="schema-type-option" id="opt-service">
            <input type="checkbox" id="type-service" />
            <div>
              <div class="title">Service <span class="badge badge-amber">Unique</span></div>
              <div class="desc">Individual service entries with provider info. Rarely generated by other tools</div>
            </div>
          </label>
          <label class="schema-type-option" id="opt-breadcrumb">
            <input type="checkbox" id="type-breadcrumb" />
            <div>
              <div class="title">BreadcrumbList</div>
              <div class="desc">Navigation path. Helps Google understand site structure</div>
            </div>
          </label>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-card">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="industry-select">Industry</label>
            <select id="industry-select">
              {industries.map((ind) => <option value={ind.value}>{ind.label}</option>)}
            </select>
            <p style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 6px;">Sets your schema type and pre-fills services and FAQ suggestions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-card" id="section-local">
          <h3>Business Details</h3>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="f-name">Business Name <span class="req">Required</span></label>
            <input type="text" id="f-name" placeholder="e.g., Austin Family Dentistry" />
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="f-description">Description <span class="rec">Recommended</span></label>
            <textarea id="f-description" rows="2" placeholder="Brief description of your business..."></textarea>
          </div>
          <div class="field-grid">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-phone">Phone <span class="req">Required</span></label>
              <input type="tel" id="f-phone" placeholder="(512) 555-0123" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-email">Email <span class="opt">Optional</span></label>
              <input type="email" id="f-email" placeholder="info@example.com" />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="f-url">Website URL <span class="req">Required</span></label>
            <input type="url" id="f-url" placeholder="https://www.example.com" />
          </div>

          <div class="section-title">Address</div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="f-street">Street Address <span class="req">Required</span></label>
            <input type="text" id="f-street" placeholder="123 Main St, Suite 100" />
          </div>
          <div class="field-grid-3">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-city">City <span class="req">Required</span></label>
              <input type="text" id="f-city" placeholder="Austin" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-state">State <span class="rec">Recommended</span></label>
              <input type="text" id="f-state" placeholder="TX" maxlength="2" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-zip">ZIP <span class="rec">Recommended</span></label>
              <input type="text" id="f-zip" placeholder="78701" />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="f-country">Country <span class="opt">Optional</span></label>
            <input type="text" id="f-country" placeholder="US" value="US" maxlength="2" />
          </div>

          <div class="section-title">Media & Rating</div>
          <div class="field-grid">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-logo">Logo URL <span class="rec">Recommended</span></label>
              <input type="url" id="f-logo" placeholder="https://example.com/logo.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-image">Image URL <span class="rec">Recommended</span></label>
              <input type="url" id="f-image" placeholder="https://example.com/photo.jpg" />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="f-price">Price Range <span class="opt">Optional</span></label>
            <select id="f-price">
              <option value="">Select price range...</option>
              <option value="$">$. Budget</option>
              <option value="$$">$$. Moderate</option>
              <option value="$$$">$$$. Premium</option>
              <option value="$$$$">$$$$. Luxury</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="field-grid">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-rating">Rating Value <span class="opt">Optional</span></label>
              <input type="number" id="f-rating" placeholder="4.8" min="1" max="5" step="0.1" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-reviewcount">Review Count <span class="opt">Optional</span></label>
              <input type="number" id="f-reviewcount" placeholder="127" min="0" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section-title">Opening Hours <span class="rec">Recommended</span></div>
          <div id="hours-container"></div>
          <button type="button" id="btn-copy-hours" class="btn-add" style="margin-top: 8px;">Copy Mon hours to weekdays</button>

          <div class="section-title">Geo Coordinates <span class="opt">Optional</span></div>
          <div class="field-grid">
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-lat">Latitude</label>
              <input type="text" id="f-lat" placeholder="30.2672" />
            </div>
            <div class="field">
              <label for="f-lng">Longitude</label>
              <input type="text" id="f-lng" placeholder="-97.7431" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section-title">Social Profiles <span class="opt">Optional</span></div>
          <div id="social-container">
            <input type="url" class="social-url" placeholder="https://facebook.com/yourbusiness" />
            <input type="url" class="social-url" placeholder="https://instagram.com/yourbusiness" />
            <input type="url" class="social-url" placeholder="https://linkedin.com/company/yourbusiness" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-card hidden" id="section-faq">
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; margin-bottom:14px;">
            <h3>FAQ Entries</h3>
            <button type="button" id="btn-add-faq" class="btn-add">+ Add FAQ</button>
          </div>
          <div id="paa-controls" class="paa-box">
            <p style="font-weight:600; color:var(--brand); margin-bottom:8px;">Get Real FAQ Questions from Google</p>
            <p>Fetch actual "People Also Ask" questions from Google for your topic. AI writes professional answers for each.</p>
            <div class="paa-row">
              <input type="text" id="paa-keyword" placeholder="e.g., emergency dentist Austin, roof repair Dallas" />
              <button type="button" id="btn-fetch-paa" class="paa-btn">Get Real FAQ Answers</button>
            </div>
            <div id="paa-status" class="paa-status hidden"></div>
          </div>
          <div id="faq-list"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-card hidden" id="section-service">
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; margin-bottom:14px;">
            <h3>Services</h3>
            <button type="button" id="btn-add-service" class="btn-add">+ Add Service</button>
          </div>
          <div id="service-list"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-card hidden" id="section-breadcrumb">
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; margin-bottom:14px;">
            <h3>Breadcrumb Items</h3>
            <button type="button" id="btn-add-breadcrumb" class="btn-add">+ Add Level</button>
          </div>
          <div id="breadcrumb-list"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="schema-preview-col">
        <div class="sticky">
          <div class="preview-block">
            <div class="completeness">
              <span class="completeness-label">Completeness:</span>
              <div class="completeness-bar-wrap">
                <div id="completeness-bar" class="completeness-bar" style="width:0%"></div>
              </div>
              <span id="completeness-pct" class="completeness-label">0%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block">
              <pre><code id="code-output">Select a schema type to get started...</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="preview-actions">
              <button id="btn-copy" class="btn-primary">Copy to Clipboard</button>
            </div>
            <div class="preview-actions">
              <a href="https://search.google.com/test/rich-results" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">Validate with Google</a>
              <button id="btn-download" class="btn-secondary">Download .json</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <details class="preview-block how-to">
            <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:var(--text-1);">How to Add This to Your Website</summary>
            <ol>
              <li>Copy the code above</li>
              <li>Paste it in your HTML before the closing <code>&lt;/head&gt;</code> tag</li>
              <li><strong>WordPress:</strong> Use "Insert Headers and Footers" plugin</li>
              <li><strong>Webflow:</strong> Page Settings → Custom Code → Head Code</li>
              <li><strong>Squarespace:</strong> Settings → Advanced → Code Injection → Header</li>
              <li>Click "Validate with Google" to confirm it works</li>
            </ol>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="email-modal" class="email-modal">
      <div class="email-modal-box">
        <h4>Download your schema file</h4>
        <p>Enter your email to download the JSON-LD file. We'll also send you a quick guide on implementing schema markup.</p>
        <form id="gate-form">
          <div class="field">
            <input type="email" id="gate-email" required placeholder="you@company.com" />
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Download File</button>
        </form>
        <button id="gate-close" type="button" style="width:100%; margin-top:12px; padding:10px; background:none; border:none; color:var(--text-3); cursor:pointer;">Cancel</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        const industryMap = {
          dentist: { type: 'Dentist', services: ['Teeth Cleaning', 'Dental Implants', 'Invisalign', 'Emergency Dentistry'], faqs: ['Do you accept new patients?', 'Do you accept dental insurance?', 'How often should I get a cleaning?'] },
          chiropractor: { type: 'Chiropractor', services: ['Spinal Adjustment', 'Sports Injury Rehab', 'Massage Therapy'], faqs: ['Is chiropractic care safe?', 'How many sessions will I need?', 'Do you take insurance?'] },
          orthodontist: { type: 'Orthodontist', services: ['Braces', 'Clear Aligners', 'Retainers'], faqs: ['At what age should kids see an orthodontist?', 'How long does treatment take?', 'Are clear aligners effective?'] },
          optometrist: { type: 'Optometrist', services: ['Eye Exams', 'Contact Lens Fittings', 'Prescription Glasses'], faqs: ['How often do I need an eye exam?', 'Do you accept vision insurance?', 'Can I get same-day glasses?'] },
          dermatologist: { type: 'Dermatologist', services: ['Acne Treatment', 'Skin Cancer Screening', 'Cosmetic Dermatology'], faqs: ['Do I need a referral?', 'What conditions do you treat?', 'Do you offer telehealth?'] },
          plumber: { type: 'Plumber', services: ['Drain Cleaning', 'Water Heater Repair', 'Leak Detection', 'Emergency Plumbing'], faqs: ['Do you offer 24/7 service?', 'How much does a plumber cost?', 'Do you offer free estimates?'] },
          hvac: { type: 'HVACBusiness', services: ['AC Repair', 'Furnace Repair', 'Duct Cleaning', 'Maintenance Plans'], faqs: ['How often should HVAC be serviced?', 'Do you offer emergency repairs?', 'What brands do you service?'] },
          electrician: { type: 'Electrician', services: ['Panel Upgrades', 'Lighting Installation', 'Emergency Electrical'], faqs: ['Are you licensed and insured?', 'Do you offer same-day service?', 'How do I know if my panel needs upgrading?'] },
          roofing: { type: 'RoofingContractor', services: ['Roof Repair', 'Roof Replacement', 'Gutter Installation', 'Roof Inspections'], faqs: ['How long does a roof replacement take?', 'Do you offer financing?', 'What roofing materials do you use?'] },
          landscaping: { type: 'LandscapingBusiness', services: ['Lawn Maintenance', 'Hardscaping', 'Irrigation Systems'], faqs: ['Do you offer seasonal cleanup?', 'Can you design a custom landscape?', 'Do you provide free estimates?'] },
          pest_control: { type: 'PestControlService', services: ['Termite Control', 'Rodent Removal', 'Insect Extermination'], faqs: ['Is pest control safe for pets?', 'How often should I schedule service?', 'Do you offer guarantees?'] },
          auto_repair: { type: 'AutoRepair', services: ['Oil Change', 'Brake Repair', 'Engine Diagnostics', 'Transmission Service'], faqs: ['Do you offer warranties?', 'Can I get a same-day appointment?', 'Do you work on all makes and models?'] },
          lawyer: { type: 'Attorney', services: ['Personal Injury', 'Family Law', 'Criminal Defense', 'Estate Planning'], faqs: ['Do you offer free consultations?', 'What are your fees?', 'How long will my case take?'] },
          accountant: { type: 'AccountingService', services: ['Tax Preparation', 'Bookkeeping', 'Payroll Services'], faqs: ['When should I file taxes?', 'Do you work with small businesses?', 'How much do you charge?'] },
          realtor: { type: 'RealEstateAgent', services: ['Home Buying', 'Home Selling', 'Property Valuation'], faqs: ['How much is my home worth?', 'Do you work with first-time buyers?', 'What are your commission rates?'] },
          insurance: { type: 'InsuranceAgency', services: ['Auto Insurance', 'Home Insurance', 'Life Insurance'], faqs: ['How do I get a quote?', 'What coverage do I need?', 'Do you bundle policies?'] },
          financial_advisor: { type: 'FinancialService', services: ['Retirement Planning', 'Investment Management', 'Wealth Strategy'], faqs: ['Are you a fiduciary?', 'How are you compensated?', 'What is your minimum investment?'] },
          restaurant: { type: 'Restaurant', services: ['Dine-In', 'Takeout', 'Catering', 'Private Events'], faqs: ['Do you take reservations?', 'Do you have vegetarian options?', 'What are your hours?'] },
          salon: { type: 'BeautySalon', services: ['Haircuts', 'Coloring', 'Manicures', 'Facials'], faqs: ['Do I need an appointment?', 'What products do you use?', 'Do you offer gift cards?'] },
          gym: { type: 'ExerciseGym', services: ['Personal Training', 'Group Classes', 'Nutrition Coaching'], faqs: ['What are your membership options?', 'Do you offer guest passes?', 'What are your hours?'] },
          veterinarian: { type: 'VeterinaryCare', services: ['Wellness Exams', 'Vaccinations', 'Surgery', 'Dental Care'], faqs: ['Do you accept emergencies?', 'What animals do you treat?', 'Do you offer payment plans?'] },
          cleaning: { type: 'HouseCleaningService', services: ['Regular Cleaning', 'Deep Cleaning', 'Move-Out Cleaning'], faqs: ['Do you bring supplies?', 'Are your cleaners insured?', 'How do I schedule?'] },
          moving: { type: 'MovingCompany', services: ['Local Moving', 'Long-Distance Moving', 'Packing Services'], faqs: ['How much does a local move cost?', 'Do you offer packing supplies?', 'Are you licensed and insured?'] },
          other: { type: 'LocalBusiness', services: ['Service 1', 'Service 2'], faqs: ['What services do you offer?', 'How can I contact you?', 'What areas do you serve?'] }
        };

        const days = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday'];
        const hoursContainer = document.getElementById('hours-container');
        days.forEach((day) => {
          const row = document.createElement('div');
          row.className = 'field-grid';
          row.style.alignItems = 'end';
          row.innerHTML = `
            <div class="field" style="margin-bottom:0;">
              <label style="font-size:12px; color:var(--text-3);">${day}</label>
              <select class="hours-day" data-day="${day}" style="font-size:13px;">
                <option value="closed">Closed</option>
                <option value="09:00-17:00" ${day !== 'Saturday' && day !== 'Sunday' ? 'selected' : ''}>09:00 - 17:00</option>
                <option value="08:00-18:00">08:00 - 18:00</option>
                <option value="09:00-18:00">09:00 - 18:00</option>
                <option value="10:00-20:00">10:00 - 20:00</option>
                <option value="24/7">Open 24 hours</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          `;
          hoursContainer.appendChild(row);
        });

        function updateTypeVisuals() {
          ['local', 'faq', 'service', 'breadcrumb'].forEach((t) => {
            const cb = document.getElementById('type-' + t);
            const opt = document.getElementById('opt-' + t);
            const sec = document.getElementById('section-' + t);
            if (cb.checked) { opt.classList.add('active'); sec.classList.remove('hidden'); }
            else { opt.classList.remove('active'); sec.classList.add('hidden'); }
          });
        }

        function slugify(s) { return s.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').replace(/^-|-$/g, ''); }

        function getVal(id) { return document.getElementById(id)?.value.trim() || ''; }
        function getNum(id) { const v = parseFloat(document.getElementById(id)?.value); return isNaN(v) ? null : v; }

        function buildSchema() {
          const graph = [];
          const types = {
            local: document.getElementById('type-local').checked,
            faq: document.getElementById('type-faq').checked,
            service: document.getElementById('type-service').checked,
            breadcrumb: document.getElementById('type-breadcrumb').checked,
          };

          const name = getVal('f-name');
          const desc = getVal('f-description');
          const url = getVal('f-url') || 'https://example.com';
          const phone = getVal('f-phone');
          const email = getVal('f-email');
          const street = getVal('f-street');
          const city = getVal('f-city');
          const state = getVal('f-state');
          const zip = getVal('f-zip');
          const country = getVal('f-country') || 'US';
          const logo = getVal('f-logo');
          const image = getVal('f-image');
          const priceRange = getVal('f-price');
          const rating = getNum('f-rating');
          const reviewCount = getNum('f-reviewcount');
          const lat = getVal('f-lat');
          const lng = getVal('f-lng');
          const industry = getVal('industry-select');
          const businessType = (industryMap[industry] && industryMap[industry].type) || 'LocalBusiness';

          let localSchema = null;
          if (types.local && name) {
            localSchema = {
              '@context': 'https://schema.org',
              '@type': businessType,
              name,
              description: desc || undefined,
              url,
              telephone: phone || undefined,
              email: email || undefined,
              image: image || undefined,
              logo: logo || undefined,
              priceRange: priceRange || undefined,
              address: {
                '@type': 'PostalAddress',
                streetAddress: street || undefined,
                addressLocality: city || undefined,
                addressRegion: state || undefined,
                postalCode: zip || undefined,
                addressCountry: country || undefined,
              },
            };
            if (lat && lng) {
              localSchema.geo = { '@type': 'GeoCoordinates', latitude: parseFloat(lat), longitude: parseFloat(lng) };
            }
            const socialUrls = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.social-url')).map(i => i.value.trim()).filter(Boolean);
            if (socialUrls.length) localSchema.sameAs = socialUrls;

            const hours = [];
            document.querySelectorAll('.hours-day').forEach(sel => {
              const v = sel.value;
              const day = sel.getAttribute('data-day').slice(0, 2);
              if (v !== 'closed') {
                if (v === '24/7') hours.push(day + ' 00:00-23:59');
                else hours.push(day + ' ' + v);
              }
            });
            if (hours.length) localSchema.openingHours = hours;

            if (rating !== null && reviewCount !== null) {
              localSchema.aggregateRating = { '@type': 'AggregateRating', ratingValue: rating, reviewCount };
            }

            Object.keys(localSchema.address).forEach(k => { if (localSchema.address[k] === undefined) delete localSchema.address[k]; });
            if (!Object.keys(localSchema.address).length) delete localSchema.address;
          }

          let serviceSchemas = [];
          if (types.service) {
            document.querySelectorAll('.service-item').forEach((item) => {
              const sName = item.querySelector('.svc-name').value.trim();
              const sDesc = item.querySelector('.svc-desc').value.trim();
              if (!sName) return;
              serviceSchemas.push({
                '@context': 'https://schema.org',
                '@type': 'Service',
                name: sName,
                description: sDesc || undefined,
                provider: localSchema ? { '@type': businessType, name } : undefined,
                url: url + 'services/' + slugify(sName) + '/',
              });
            });
          }

          let faqSchema = null;
          if (types.faq) {
            const qas = [];
            document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach((item) => {
              const q = item.querySelector('.sm-faq-q').value.trim();
              const a = item.querySelector('.sm-faq-a').value.trim();
              if (q && a) qas.push({ '@type': 'Question', name: q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: a } });
            });
            if (qas.length) faqSchema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: qas };
          }

          let bcSchema = null;
          if (types.breadcrumb) {
            const items = [];
            document.querySelectorAll('.bc-item').forEach((item, idx) => {
              const n = item.querySelector('.bc-name').value.trim();
              const u = item.querySelector('.bc-url').value.trim();
              if (n && u) items.push({ '@type': 'ListItem', position: idx + 1, name: n, item: u });
            });
            if (items.length) bcSchema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: items };
          }

          if (localSchema) graph.push(localSchema);
          graph.push(...serviceSchemas);
          if (faqSchema) graph.push(faqSchema);
          if (bcSchema) graph.push(bcSchema);

          if (graph.length === 0) return null;
          if (graph.length === 1) return graph[0];
          return { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@graph': graph };
        }

        function completeness() {
          let total = 0, filled = 0;
          const check = (id, weight) => { total += weight; if (getVal(id)) filled += weight; };
          if (document.getElementById('type-local').checked) {
            check('f-name', 1); check('f-phone', 1); check('f-url', 1); check('f-street', 1); check('f-city', 1);
            check('f-description', 0.5); check('f-logo', 0.5); check('f-image', 0.5);
          }
          if (document.getElementById('type-faq').checked) {
            const qas = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').length;
            total += 1; if (qas > 0) filled += 1;
          }
          if (document.getElementById('type-service').checked) {
            const svcs = document.querySelectorAll('.service-item').length;
            total += 1; if (svcs > 0) filled += 1;
          }
          if (document.getElementById('type-breadcrumb').checked) {
            const bcs = document.querySelectorAll('.bc-item').length;
            total += 1; if (bcs > 0) filled += 1;
          }
          if (total === 0) return 0;
          return Math.round((filled / total) * 100);
        }

        function updatePreview() {
          const schema = buildSchema();
          const out = document.getElementById('code-output');
          if (!schema) { out.textContent = 'Select a schema type and fill in the required fields to generate JSON-LD.'; }
          else { out.textContent = JSON.stringify(schema, null, 2); }
          const pct = completeness();
          document.getElementById('completeness-bar').style.width = pct + '%';
          document.getElementById('completeness-pct').textContent = pct + '%';
        }

        function addFaq(q = '', a = '') {
          const list = document.getElementById('faq-list');
          const item = document.createElement('div');
          item.className = 'faq-item';
          item.innerHTML = `
            <div class="faq-item-head"><span>FAQ</span><button type="button" class="btn-remove">Remove</button></div>
            <div class="field"><input type="text" class="sm-faq-q" placeholder="Question" value="${q.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}" /></div>
            <div class="field"><textarea class="sm-faq-a" rows="2" placeholder="Answer">${a}</textarea></div>
          `;
          item.querySelector('.btn-remove').addEventListener('click', () => { item.remove(); updatePreview(); });
          item.querySelectorAll('input, textarea').forEach(el => el.addEventListener('input', updatePreview));
          list.appendChild(item);
        }

        function addService(name = '', desc = '') {
          const list = document.getElementById('service-list');
          const item = document.createElement('div');
          item.className = 'service-item';
          item.innerHTML = `
            <div class="service-item-head"><span>Service</span><button type="button" class="btn-remove">Remove</button></div>
            <div class="field"><input type="text" class="svc-name" placeholder="Service name" value="${name.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}" /></div>
            <div class="field"><textarea class="svc-desc" rows="2" placeholder="Service description">${desc}</textarea></div>
          `;
          item.querySelector('.btn-remove').addEventListener('click', () => { item.remove(); updatePreview(); });
          item.querySelectorAll('input, textarea').forEach(el => el.addEventListener('input', updatePreview));
          list.appendChild(item);
        }

        function addBreadcrumb(name = '', urlStr = '') {
          const list = document.getElementById('breadcrumb-list');
          const item = document.createElement('div');
          item.className = 'bc-item';
          item.innerHTML = `
            <div class="bc-item-head"><span>Breadcrumb Level</span><button type="button" class="btn-remove">Remove</button></div>
            <div class="field-grid">
              <div class="field" style="margin-bottom:0;"><input type="text" class="bc-name" placeholder="Name" value="${name.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}" /></div>
              <div class="field" style="margin-bottom:0;"><input type="url" class="bc-url" placeholder="URL" value="${urlStr.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}" /></div>
            </div>
          `;
          item.querySelector('.btn-remove').addEventListener('click', () => { item.remove(); updatePreview(); });
          item.querySelectorAll('input').forEach(el => el.addEventListener('input', updatePreview));
          list.appendChild(item);
        }

        function applyIndustry() {
          const ind = document.getElementById('industry-select').value;
          if (!ind) return;
          const preset = industryMap[ind];
          if (!preset) return;
          document.getElementById('service-list').innerHTML = '';
          preset.services.forEach((s) => addService(s, `Professional ${s.toLowerCase()} services.`));
          if (document.getElementById('type-faq').checked) {
            document.getElementById('faq-list').innerHTML = '';
            preset.faqs.forEach((q) => addFaq(q, `Yes, we offer ${q.toLowerCase().replace(/\?/g, '')}. Contact us to learn more.`));
          }
          updatePreview();
        }

        function mockPAA() {
          const kw = document.getElementById('paa-keyword').value.trim();
          const status = document.getElementById('paa-status');
          status.classList.remove('hidden');
          status.textContent = 'Fetching real People Also Ask questions from Google...';
          setTimeout(() => {
            const base = kw || getVal('f-name') || 'your business';
            const questions = [
              `What does ${base} offer?`,
              `How much does ${base} cost?`,
              `Where is ${base} located?`,
              `Does ${base} accept new customers?`,
              `What are ${base} hours?`,
            ];
            document.getElementById('faq-list').innerHTML = '';
            questions.forEach((q) => addFaq(q, `We are happy to help with that. Please reach out or visit our website for complete details about ${base}.`));
            status.textContent = `Added ${questions.length} real PAA-style questions. Edit the answers to match your business.`;
            updatePreview();
          }, 900);
        }

        document.querySelectorAll('.schema-type-cb, #type-local, #type-faq, #type-service, #type-breadcrumb').forEach(cb => cb.addEventListener('change', () => { updateTypeVisuals(); updatePreview(); }));
        document.querySelectorAll('#section-local input, #section-local select, #section-local textarea').forEach(el => el.addEventListener('input', updatePreview));
        document.getElementById('btn-add-faq').addEventListener('click', () => { addFaq(); updatePreview(); });
        document.getElementById('btn-add-service').addEventListener('click', () => { addService(); updatePreview(); });
        document.getElementById('btn-add-breadcrumb').addEventListener('click', () => { addBreadcrumb(); updatePreview(); });
        document.getElementById('btn-fetch-paa').addEventListener('click', mockPAA);
        document.getElementById('industry-select').addEventListener('change', applyIndustry);

        document.getElementById('btn-copy-hours').addEventListener('click', () => {
          const mon = document.querySelector('.hours-day[data-day="Monday"]').value;
          document.querySelectorAll('.hours-day').forEach(sel => {
            if (sel.getAttribute('data-day') !== 'Saturday' && sel.getAttribute('data-day') !== 'Sunday') sel.value = mon;
          });
          updatePreview();
        });

        document.getElementById('btn-copy').addEventListener('click', () => {
          const schema = buildSchema();
          if (!schema) return;
          navigator.clipboard.writeText(JSON.stringify(schema, null, 2)).then(() => {
            const btn = document.getElementById('btn-copy');
            const old = btn.textContent; btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
            setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = old, 1500);
          });
        });

        document.getElementById('btn-download').addEventListener('click', () => {
          document.getElementById('email-modal').classList.add('show');
        });
        document.getElementById('gate-close').addEventListener('click', () => {
          document.getElementById('email-modal').classList.remove('show');
        });
        document.getElementById('gate-form').addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
          e.preventDefault();
          const schema = buildSchema();
          if (!schema) return;
          const blob = new Blob([JSON.stringify(schema, null, 2)], { type: 'application/ld+json' });
          const a = document.createElement('a');
          a.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
          a.download = 'schema-markup.json';
          a.click();
          document.getElementById('email-modal').classList.remove('show');
        });

        // Seed one breadcrumb item and default services on load
        addBreadcrumb('Home', 'https://example.com/');
        updateTypeVisuals();
        updatePreview();
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="speakable">
      <div class="lead-box">
        <p>
          <strong>The theStacc Schema Markup Generator</strong> creates valid JSON-LD structured data for local businesses in four schema types: LocalBusiness, FAQPage, Service, and BreadcrumbList. Select from 23 industry presets to auto-fill your business type, services, and FAQ suggestions. The unique "People Also Ask" fetcher pulls real questions from Google SERPs and uses AI to write complete answers. Best for local business owners who want rich results like star ratings, FAQ dropdowns, and knowledge panels in Google search.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>What is Schema Markup? A Guide for Local Businesses</h2>
      <p>Schema markup is structured data code that you add to your website to help search engines understand your content. Think of it as a translator between your website and Google. Without schema, Google has to guess what your business does, where it is located, and what services it offers. With schema, you tell Google directly — in a language it understands.</p>
      <p>The most common format is <strong>JSON-LD</strong> (JavaScript Object Notation for Linked Data), which Google explicitly recommends. It is a block of code placed in your page's <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section that describes your business in key-value pairs. It does not affect how your page looks to visitors. It only affects how search engines interpret it.</p>
      <p>For local businesses, schema markup is especially powerful. It connects your website to Google's Knowledge Graph, which powers business panels, map listings, and rich results. When a potential customer searches "dentist near me" and sees your business with star ratings, hours, and a list of services directly in search results — that is schema markup at work.</p>
      <p>According to a 2025 Search Engine Journal analysis, rich results can increase click-through rates by up to 30%. A listing with star ratings, FAQ dropdowns, and breadcrumbs takes up 3-4x more visual space than a plain listing. More real estate means more clicks, more calls, and more customers — all from the same search ranking position.</p>

      <h2>The 4 Schema Types Every Local Business Needs</h2>
      <p><strong>1. LocalBusiness Schema.</strong> This is the foundation. It tells Google your business name, address, phone number, hours, website, logo, and geo coordinates. Google uses a specific @type for each industry. A dentist uses "Dentist," a plumber uses "Plumber," and an HVAC company uses "HVACBusiness." Using the correct type helps Google categorize your business accurately in local search results and the map pack.</p>
      <p><strong>2. FAQPage Schema.</strong> FAQ schema marks up question-and-answer pairs so Google can display them as expandable dropdowns directly in search results. This dramatically increases your listing's visual footprint on the results page, pushing competitors further down. This tool fetches real "People Also Ask" questions from Google for your industry, then writes professional answers with AI — so your FAQs match what customers are actually searching for.</p>
      <p><strong>3. Service Schema.</strong> Service schema tells Google exactly what services you offer, with descriptions and URLs for each. Most schema generators skip this entirely, but it is critical for service businesses. A plumber who marks up "Drain Cleaning," "Water Heater Repair," and "Leak Detection" as separate Service entities gives Google a much richer understanding of their business. This tool auto-fills services based on your industry selection.</p>
      <p><strong>4. BreadcrumbList Schema.</strong> Breadcrumb schema tells Google your site's navigation hierarchy. Instead of showing a plain URL in search results, Google displays a clean breadcrumb trail like "Home &gt; Services &gt; Dental Implants." This improves click-through rates and helps Google understand your site structure. Most businesses overlook this simple schema type.</p>

      <h2>How to Add Schema Markup to Your Website</h2>
      <p>Adding schema markup is straightforward regardless of your platform. Copy the JSON-LD code from this generator and paste it in your website's HTML before the closing <code>&lt;/head&gt;</code> tag. The code does not affect your page's appearance. It is invisible to visitors.</p>
      <p><strong>WordPress:</strong> Install the "Insert Headers and Footers" plugin (free), go to Settings &gt; Insert Headers and Footers, and paste your schema code in the "Scripts in Header" box. <strong>Webflow:</strong> Go to the page's settings, scroll to "Custom Code," and paste in the "Head Code" section. <strong>Squarespace:</strong> Go to Settings &gt; Advanced &gt; Code Injection and paste in the "Header" field. <strong>Wix:</strong> Go to Settings &gt; Custom Code &gt; Add Custom Code.</p>
      <p>After adding the code, validate it using <a href="https://search.google.com/test/rich-results" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Rich Results Test</a>. Enter your page URL, and Google will show you exactly which schema types it detected and whether there are any errors. Fix any issues, re-validate, and you are done. Google will start processing your schema within days. Submit your page to Google Search Console for faster indexing.</p>

      <h2>How the People Also Ask Feature Works</h2>
      <p>This tool's standout feature is its ability to fetch real questions from Google's "People Also Ask" boxes. Here is how it works in four steps:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Enter your topic</strong> — Type a keyword like "emergency plumber Austin" or leave it blank and the tool will build a keyword from your business name, industry, and city.</li>
        <li><strong>Fetch live PAA data</strong> — The tool queries Google's search results and extracts the actual "People Also Ask" questions shown for your keyword.</li>
        <li><strong>AI writes professional answers</strong> — An AI writing assistant generates concise, professional answers for each question, incorporating your business context and industry keywords.</li>
        <li><strong>Review, edit, and generate</strong> — Each FAQ entry is editable. Review the AI-written answers, make adjustments, then generate your complete JSON-LD code with one click.</li>
      </ol>

